name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: The prior administration rolled back our efforts to ensure clean water for Washingtonians. Today, our strong water standards are back. Thank you @EPA. This is good news for Washington families, Tribes and fish.

name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: Washington stands with Ukraine. Volunteers and regional leaders have gathered 32 tons of emergency medical supplies that are being loaded right now to help Ukrainian hospitals and families. name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: I am committed to working with the community, fellow elected state leaders, the Biden Administration, and our Congressional delegation to put the Hanford cleanup on a sustainable path. We can’t wait until the 22nd century. It’s time to meet our moral and legal obligations NOW.

name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: Washington state is committed to working with @ENERGY, @EPA, and @POTUS to safely and quickly clean up Hanford. But it’s crunchtime now. The decisions we make today will have consequences for generations to come.

name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: These cuts would happen at a time good progress is underway at Hanford. This year the Tank Side Cesium Removal facility opened. Processing of low-activity waste will begin next year. If the federal government pulls back its obligations, this cleanup will last into next century.

name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: Failure to cleanup at the Hanford Site isn’t an option. Tens of millions of tons of dangerous waste remain on site. Tanks continue to leak. The cost of failure at Hanford will be borne by the Tri-Cities community, farmers, Tribes, and on the Columbia River.

name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: There is a great deal to like about President Biden's 2023 budget request. I am concerned, however, about the apparent decision to request substantial cuts to the budget for cleaning up the Hanford Site. Now is the time to redouble our efforts at Hanford, not to curtail them.

name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: Another tragic loss on an already dark day for our law enforcement community. Our thoughts are with Officer Rocha's wife, sons and family.

name: Governor Jay Inslee
tweet: I also enjoyed answering questions about homelessness policies at the @SeattleChamber’s Regional Leadership Conference at Suncadia today. We made great investments in more units this session, but we need to do more, especially on middle housing.  https://t.co/gVJh57ofz6
